OL,4,CGovernment apologises over failure to
OL,5,Ccommemorate black and Asian troops
OL,6, The government has apologised for
OL,7, failures to properly commemorate black
OL,8, and Asian troops who died in World War
OL,9, One fighting for the British Empire.
OL,11,FSome troops were commemorated
OL,12,Fcollectively or their names were
OL,13,Frecorded in registers, while their
OL,14,Fwhite counterparts had headstones.
OL,16,FA report by the Commonwealth War Graves
OL,17,FCommission found the reason for this
OL,18,Fwas "pervasive racism".
OL,20,FIn the Commons, Defence Secretary Ben
OL,21,FWallace expressed "deep regret".
